  "correct_answer": "Force spread over an area",
  "explanation": "Pressure is defined as force divided by the area over which that force acts. It measures how concentrated or spread out a force is. The formula is pressure = force ÷ area. This is why sharp objects (small area) create higher pressure than blunt objects (large area) when the same force is applied.",
